l; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">They last thoughout the ages </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">My grandfather''s favourite fairytale </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Or the science gathered among the pages </span></pre>\n<pre></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">And these words bring people together </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Language unites and sets us free </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">But it is same words that bind us </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">As when two different cultures meet. </span></pre>\n<pre>\n\n</pre>', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2015-06-06 23:12:29', '2015-06-06 17:42:29', '', 0, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/?p=225', 0, 'post', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(146, 1, '2015-04-25 19:37:28', '2015-04-25 14:07:28', 'Another Saturday night. The whole world seems to be lost in the dance floor; making temporary friends and washed out memories. Tantalizing. With a sombre mind and a half-hearted attempt to "dress for the occasion", you grab the handle of the door and stop midway. The One beckons you and you know there is no further questioning.\r\n\r\nYou delve into the familiar pages of your all-time favourite book.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/stock-footage-fireplace-and-a-book.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-143 aligncenter" src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/stock-footage-fireplace-and-a-book-300x168.jpg" alt="stock-footage-fireplace-and-a-book" width="431" height="246" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDrowning in nostalgia and mingled with the hope of finding something new, this book has and always will be a part of your soul. The pages bear unforgettable scents, each more homely than the last. The words pour out of you as if you lived to write the chapters in this story. You create irreplaceable bonds with every character. As you grow older, you discover new insights and perceptions about the story, the character. You might have hated the antagonist but now you admire his stand. Teary eyed, you cursed the author for the death of your favourite character but now you understand why which makes the book even more beautiful.  When you finished reading it the first time, you knew this love affair would not be fading away.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cropped-shutterstock_86389951.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-144 aligncenter" src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cropped-shutterstock_86389951-300x123.jpg" alt="cropped-shutterstock_86389951" width="512" height="220" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWine and coffee tastes better when accompanied with the One. Reality does not compare when you immerse yourself in the world you wish you could see. People who like the One automatically become your best friends. Different books by the same author may or may not (mostly not) be as good as this work of gold. No matter what people say, the movie will NEVER be better.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Writers-Cabaret-Option-1.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-145 aligncenter" src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Writers-Cabaret-Option-1-200x300.jpg" alt="Writers Cabaret Option 1" width="306" height="451" /></a>\r\n\r\nFor those of you who haven''t experienced the euphoria of finding your favourite book, keep looking. For it is a key to a secret world that only you know of. In this dark world of despair and betrayal, no one can destroy the liaison between man and book.\r\n\r\nWho''s the One for you?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The One', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '140-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-25 19:37:28', '2015-04-25 14:07:28', '', 140, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/140-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(45, 1, '2015-03-22 19:34:40', '2015-03-22 14:04:40', '<p>For some, it is their favorite pastime whereas, for some, reading is the best way to take their minds off of the troubles of daily life. Each one of us needs an activity that can calm our minds and rejuvenate our body after we have spent the whole day running from one place to another, either completing errands, or living up to our boss’ expectations. Reading is an activity that can only benefit the reader and can never harm him if done for the purpose of recreation.</p>\r\n<p>A recent biological study claims that for each new thought that a human brain thinks of, a new branch is created inside it, which results in an increase in the speed of impulse transfer, hence improving the brain’s processing speed. Now keep this fact in mind and think of an avid reader- a reader who indulges himself in reading materials that make him imagine things he has never imagined before. Each imagination, a new thought. Each new thought, a new brain branch. No wonder most of the geniuses that the world has ever seen had/have reading as an integral part of their daily lives.</p>\r\n<p>Studies have also shown that staying mentally stimulated can slow the progress of (or possibly even prevent) Alzheimer’s and Dementia, since keeping your brain active and engaged prevents it from losing power.</p>\r\n<p>Reading can be of various forms. People read newspapers, journals, novels, blogs, and various other rich text. However, reading a novel is the most consuming of all. This is simply because if a person starts reading a novel of his interest, it is nearly impossible for him to leave it without completing it, as each line of a novel says a new story. Each new line drowns the reader into deeper and deeper thoughts. This is the kind of craving that reading creates.</p>\r\n<p>The answer to the question that what a novel transforms a person into, is not a simple one. It obviously is not something involving calculus, but it is complex because there are so many things that a person changes into while reading, that it is quite difficult to document it in one place. However, by the means of this article, I will try my best to throw as much light as possible on the various transformations.</p>\r\n<p>As I already mentioned earlier, many people use novel reading as a recreational way for <b>stress reduction</b>. A person, if inculcates a regular reading habit, he is less susceptible to breaking down under pressure than his counterparts who are not in a habit of reading. No matter how much stress he has at work, in his relationships or in other issues faced in everyday life, all that just slips away when he involves himself into a great story. A well-written novel has the capability to transport a person under stress to other realms, allowing him to drain his problems out of his mind and to relax. In addition to the relaxation that accompanies reading a good book, it is possible that the subject being read by a person can bring about <b>immense inner peace and tranquility</b>.Reading spiritual texts can lower blood pressure and bring about an immense peace, while reading self-help books has helped people suffering from certain mood disorders and mild mental illnesses.</p>\r\n<p>One of the most sought after gems in a person’s language is his <b>vocabulary</b>. A novel can transform an average language user into someone who has a vast vocabulary and has the capability to impress people listening to him or reading his work by the use of such subtle but highly impactite words. A large vocabulary also boosts a person’s self-esteem, his confidence, and may also prove as a very helpful aid in his career, especially if his job requires communicating with people.  In addition to increased vocabulary, a novel improves a person’s <b>writing skills</b>. This can directly be inferred from the fact that an increase in vocabulary means better usage of words and thus, improved writing. Observing the cadence, fluidity and writing styles of other authors influences one’s own work. Just as musicians influence one another, and painters use techniques established by previous masters, so do writers learn how to craft prose by reading the works of others.</p>\r\n<p>Besides vocabulary, who can forget to mention what novels give a person the most - <b>knowledge</b>. Everything a person reads, fills his head with new bits of information, which might come in handy anytime. Also, a thing to remember is that a person might lose everything in life, his job, his house, his money - but no one has the power to take away his knowledge from him.</p>\r\n<p>A book is said to be one of the easiest and the best ways for <b>memory improvement</b>. But how can storytelling improve memory? This is because each novel has an assortment of characters; each character has its own history, ambitions, and nuances, as well as the various arcs and sub-plots weaving their way throughout the novel which ought to be remembered if the whole of the story has to be understood.</p>\r\n<p>In our Internet-crazed world, attention is drawn in a million different directions at once as we multi-task throughout the day. But when a person reads a book of his interest, his entire attention is focused just on the story - the rest of the world just falls away, and the reader immerses in every fine detail he is absorbing. One should try reading for 15-20 minutes every day before starting his daily activities and he’ll be surprised at the increased amount of focus he’s able to give to all activities he involves himself in.</p>\r\n<p>At last, it is clear that reading transforms a person into someone entirely different. The icing on the cake, all these benefits come for free! Sure some of us buy books, but most books are available either for free or at meager costs at local libraries, or on the Internet. There’s a genre for every literate person on our planet, and whether your taste lies in classical literature, poetry, fashion magazines, religious texts, biographies, young adult books or romantic novels, there’s something out there to capture your curiosity and imagination. So step away from meaningless activities for a little while, crack open a book or an e-book, and replenish your soul for a little while.</p>\r\n', 'Books full of words, a life full of experiences', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'books-full-of-words-a-life-full-of-experiences-3', '', '', '2015-04-08 15:20:50', '2015-04-08 09:50:50', '', 0, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/?p=45', 0, 'post', '', 9);
